Write a function maxInArray that takes arr as an argument and returns the maximum element in the array.

Use a loop in your solution. The use of the Math.max () method is not permitted.

Example:

maxInArray ([3, 4, 8, 1]) should return 8;
maxInArray ([11, 12) should return 12;
maxInArray ([1, 1]) should return 1;
maxInArray ([]) should return undefined.

Solution:

function maxInArray(arr){
  let max = arr[0];
  for(let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
   if (arr[i] > max) max = arr[i];
  }
  return max;
}
